{
  "texts": [
    "Cultures were grown for an additional 4 h at 37 °C and 250 r.p.m.",
    "and subsequently centrifuged (3500 × g, 4 °C, 10 min).",
    "Supernatant was removed, and cell pellets were resuspended in 1 ml PBS.",
    "One hundred microliters of the cell resuspension for each condition was transferred to a 96-well microtiter plate, from which the fluorescence (excitation, 485 nm; emission, 509 nm) and absorbance (600 nm) were measured using the Tecan Infinite M1000 plate reader.",
    "Clones with the highest signal-to-noise ratio (generally the top 5-10% of the screened clones) were then sequenced and subcloned into a fresh pReg-RamR vector."
  ]
}